Region Combinations should be edited to:
Region Combinations

Regions can be inverted, combined, subtracted, intersected, translated or mirrored by putting them inside of the following elements.

<negative><region name="opti-region"/></negative>
<!-- Inverse of a region -->

<union><region name="region1"/><region name="region2"/>..</union>
<!-- Combination of multiple regions -->

<complement><region name="region1"/><region name="region2"/>..</complement>
<!-- Subtracts successive regions from the first defined region -->

<intersect><region name="region1"/><region name="region2"/>..</intersect>
<!-- Returns the area that multiple regions intersect with -->

<translate offset="x,y,z"><region name="region1"/></translate>
<!-- Creates a new region with the same size and shape of the referenced region, but at a location defined by the offset -->

<mirror region="region1" normal="1,0,0"/> 
<!-- mirror a particular region on the Z axis -->

<mirror origin="100,50,30" normal="1,0,0"/> 
<!-- mirror on the X axis about the point 100,50,30 -->
